# rx_y4_p — Rx(-p·π/4), Yoshida-4 X-field coefficient rotation. analytic golden.
```python id=bloq
import numpy as np
from qualtran.bloqs.basic_gates import Rx
p=1/(4-4**(1/3)); q=1-4*p
bloq = Rx(-p*np.pi/4)
```
```python id=golden
import numpy as np
p=1/(4-4**(1/3)); q=1-4*p
X = np.array([[0,1],[1,0]], complex)
golden = (np.cos(p*np.pi/8)*np.eye(2) + 1j*np.sin(p*np.pi/8)*X).astype(complex)
```
